This is the Cyclictest benchmark ported to RTEMS.

Cyclictest measures the difference between expected and actual wake-up
time of a high-priority thread. It uses clock_nanosleep() with
TIMER_ABSTIME for precise periodic timing, and clock_gettime() for
high-resolution timestamps.

The test runs a configurable number of iterations (default: 10000)
with a configurable interval (default: 1000 us). After completion,
it prints min/avg/max latency statistics.

Configuration:
  INTERVAL_US       - Measurement interval in microseconds
  MAX_CYCLES        - Number of cycles (0 = infinite)
  PRIORITY          - Measurement task priority
  PRINT_INTERVAL    - Intermediate output frequency
